definition.value: An amino trisaccharide that is D-mannopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 have each been converted into the corresponding 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl derivatives.
A alpha-D-Glcp-(1->4)-[alpha-D-Glcp-(1->6)]-D-Glcp which has alpha- configuration at the anomeric carbon of the non-terminal glucopyranose ring.
A disaccharride consisting of beta-D-xylopyranose and alpha-D-mannopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.

An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residue, two beta-D-mannopyranose residues and a beta-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by (1->2), (1->2), and (1->4) glycosidic bonds.
A trisaccharide consisting of two beta-D-glucopyranose residues and a beta-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by (1->4) glycosidic bonds.

An amino disaccharide that is 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 has been converted to the corresponding D-galactopyranoside. The stereochemistry at the anomeric position in each of the galactopyranose rings is not stated.
An amino disaccharide that is 2-acetamido-alpha-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 has been converted into the corresponding beta-L-fucopyranoside.
